serve that generally higher ? leads to lower error, probably 
because more information is captured in the normalized fea-
tures than in the moments. After all, moments only capture 
general statistics, whereas the features have many channels 
and can capture texture information in great detail. We also 
investigate various values of the exchange probability p (for 
fixed ? = 0.9), but on the ImageNet data p = 1 (i.e. apply 
MoEx on every image) tends to perform best.
